{#
  Deflect prompt — KB-only resolution path. No autonomous tool calls
  besides kb.search are expected.

  Context variables:
    customer_question: string
    kb_excerpts: list[ {title, snippet, url} ]
#}
The customer asked:

  "{{ customer_question }}"

You have the following knowledge-base excerpts. Use them, and them only,
to answer. Do not assert anything you cannot back from these excerpts.

{% for excerpt in kb_excerpts | default([]) -%}
[{{ loop.index }}] {{ excerpt.title }}
{{ excerpt.snippet }}
({{ excerpt.url | default("kb://internal") }})

{% endfor %}

If the excerpts do not cover the question, say so and offer to open a
ticket. Do not call any non-KB tool in this turn.

Write a reply of at most 4 sentences in plain language. End with a single
follow-up question that confirms the customer's issue is resolved.
